      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EURO KEEPING (2) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 3.5 lengths third (30.05) in a Grade 5 at Wentworth Park. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Capable of going well again. HARD SNIFF STYLE (1) claimed maiden win two back then finished a 4.5 lengths third last start at this track over 520m (30.09). Returns to the scene of his maiden win. Rates a winning chance on best. GULL WING (7) unfancied latest but hit the ground running and gave a sight, holding on for a minor placing (30.34) at this track in a Mix over 520m. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Hard to beat again. ZHANG (8) hasn't been far away, finishing in the money twice in a row including last time in a Mix at this track over 520m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw.",
